"{\"abstract\":\"In a Periodic Double Auction (PDA), there are multiple discrete trading periods for a single type of good. PDAs are commonly used in real-world energy markets to trade energy in specific time slots to balance demand on the power grid. Strategically, bidding in a PDA is complicated because the bidder must predict and plan for future auctions that may influence the bidding strategy for the current auction. We present a general bidding strategy for PDAs based on forecasting clearing prices and using Monte Carlo Tree Search (MCTS) to plan a bidding strategy across multiple time periods. In addition, we present a fast heuristic strategy that can be used either as a standalone method or as an initial set of bids to seed the MCTS policy. We evaluate our bidding strategies using a PDA simulator based on the wholesale market implemented in the Power Trading Agent Competition (PowerTAC) competition. We demonstrate that our strategies outperform state-of-the-art bidding strategies designed for that competition.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"3366128\",\"name\":\"Moinul Morshed Porag Chowdhury\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/3366128\"},{\"authorId\":\"1801567\",\"name\":\"Christopher Kiekintveld\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1801567\"},{\"authorId\":\"143822794\",\"name\":\"S. Tran\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/143822794\"},{\"authorId\":\"1805457\",\"name\":\"William Yeoh\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1805457\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"1409358066\",\"name\":\"Jannick Hemelhof\"},{\"authorId\":\"121947924\",\"name\":\"M. Mihaylov\"},{\"authorId\":\"144336828\",\"name\":\"A. Now\\u00e9\"}],\"doi\":null,\"intent\":[\"background\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"47abd4c4d6b9f5812078df7ebec88dbfb2e2ec2f\",\"title\":\"Improving Zero-Intelligence Plus for Call Markets\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticsc